Press Releases.Title: No New Cases of Locally Transmitted Covid-19 Infection
Press Releases.MainContent:
As of 8 December 2020, 12pm, the Ministry of Health (MOH) has preliminarily confirmed that there are no new cases of locally transmitted COVID-19 infection. 

2          There are 12 imported cases, who had already been placed on Stay-Home Notice upon arrival in Singapore. 

3         We are still working through the details of the cases, and further updates will be shared via the MOH press release that will be issued tonight. 

MINISTRY OF HEALTH
8 DECEMBER 2020
